From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000003 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: polyregion <noreply@polyregion>
Date: Sun, 08 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [SPIRV] legalize a scalar store through a ptrcast to an array
 dest

SPIRVLegalizePointerCast::transformStore handles a store whose pointer is a
ptrcast: struct dest (store to first member), vector<-vector, vector<-scalar
(first element), and array<-vector. It was missing array<-scalar: storing a
scalar through a pointer the backend deduced as an array element type. This
arises whenever an element-0 access of a fixed local array folds to the array
base (`getelementptr [N x T], p, 0, 0` -> `p`), so the store's pointer is the
[N x T] alloca but the value is a single T. Without this case the pass hits
`llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ptrcast use in store")`. storeToFirstValueAggregate
already builds the recursive GEP-to-first-element chain (handles arrays), so route
array<-scalar there, mirroring the existing vector<-scalar case.
---
 llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp b/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp
--- a/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Target/SPIRV/SPIRVLegalizePointerCast.cpp
@@ -370,6 +370,8 @@ class SPIRVLegalizePointerCast : public FunctionPass {
       storeToFirstValueAggregate(B, Src, Dst, D_VT, Alignment);
     else if (D_AT && S_VT && S_VT->getElementType() == D_AT->getElementType())
       storeArrayFromVector(B, Src, Dst, D_AT, Alignment);
+    else if (D_AT && !S_VT && isTypeFirstElementAggregate(FromTy, D_AT))
+      storeToFirstValueAggregate(B, Src, Dst, D_AT, Alignment);
     else
       llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ptrcast use in store. Please fix.");

